The Purpose of This Release

	This patch release contains approximately one hundred (100) bug 
	fixes for the OSF/Motif 1.2 source code base. The number of
	Change Requests (CRs) resolved for this release is approximately
	one hundred and fifty (150).  All fixes were implemented in the
 	./lib/Xm source code.

	This patch release contains source code addressing defects reported
	against versions up through Release 1.2.4.  In addition, this patch
	release includes new functionality and enhancements to converge the
	OSF/Motif source code with the Common Desktop Environment (CDE) 1.0
	version of Motif.  Please refer to the section of this document
	entitled "New Functionality and Enhancements to support the
	Common Desktop Environment (CDE)".

	The reference platforms for Motif 1.2.5 are the HP 9000/720
	running HP-UX 9.01 and an Intel 486 workstation running OSF/1
	1.2.

	Motif 1.2.5 is 64-bit clean using the DEC Alpha OSF/1
	V1.3 Rev. 111 as the test platform.

	OSF encourages the reporting of all bugs found in OSF/Motif
	regardless of the platform or hardware configuration in which
	the bug is found.  However, OSF will commit to accept (and
	repair according to priority) only those bugs that can be
	replicated on the current reference configurations.  A list of
	known bugs can be found in the OPENBUGS file and a list of
	bugs fixed in this release can be found in the CLOSEDBUGS file,
	both on the release media.

	In addition, OSF has added a list of bugs that we do not intend 
	to fix.  These bugs can be found in the WILLNOTFIXBUGS file.  In 
	the majority of cases, the reason we do not intend to fix these 
	bugs is because doing so would create larger problems for our
        Motif Software Support subscribers.

	Since this is a general availability product release, it has
	undergone the full quality assurance cycle at OSF.


Installing This Release

	OSF/Motif 1.2.5 is provided on magnetic tape, in tar format.

	This release is made up of a "sparse tree" of files that have
	changed since patch release 1.2.4. The new versions of the
	files should replace the corresponding Motif 1.2.4 versions of
	the files in your source tree, and then the Makefiles and then
	the binaries should be rebuilt.


	Before you install this release, you must have installed patch
	releases 1.2.1, 1.2.2, 1.2.3 and 1.2.4. 

	To install the entire contents of the tape, create the directory
	that you want to be the root for the sources, make that the current 
	directory, load the tape into the tape drive, and issue this 
	command:

		tar xvf device_name

	After the tape is unloaded, you can use, for example, the cp -f
	command to copy the sources from the current directory into
	your source tree.


