New Functionality and Enhancements to support the Common Desktop 
Environment (CDE)

	This release includes new functionality and enhancements to
	converge OSF/Motif 1.2 source code with the Common Desktop 
	Environment's version of Motif. 

	New Functionality:

	* Complete localization of toolkit error messages
	
	* XmGetPixmap() and XmGetPixmapByDepth() use the environmental variable
	  XMICONSEARCHPATH or XMICONBMSEARCHPATH as the icon search path. If
	  neither of these variables is set, then they use XBLANGPATH, which
	  is the OSF/Motif behavior.


	Enhancements:

	* Optionally allowing mouse button 2 on a three-button mouse to be used
	  to extend the current selection. This is equivalent to the OPEN LOOK 
	  Adjust function.

	* Allowing Tab to be used to move through a group of PushButton widgets
	  and gadgets, ArrowButton widgets and gadgets, and DrawnButton widgets 
	  and gadgets.

	* Allowing mouse button 3 to activate a CascadeButton menu.

	* Providing three new resources{pathMode, fileFilterStyle and 
	  dirTextLabelString} for the XmFileSelectionBox widget.

	* Allowing multiple virtual key bindings.

	* Providing visual enhancements.


	Each of the preceding enchancements can be controlled by a resource:
	either a widget resource or an application-wide resource. The
	default values for this resource provide behavior and API's that are
	identical to that of OSF/Motif 1.2.4. In addition, each of the 
	enhancements has a unique "ifdef" that can be set in the 
	./lib/Xm/Imakefile.

	
